[[File:Romany musician.jpg|right|thumb|A '''Rom''' (Romani) musician in the Czech Republic.]]

===Etymology 1===
From {{bor|en|rom|rrom|t=Romani man}}, probably ultimately from {{der|en|sa|डोम|t=member of a low caste of travelling musicians and dancers}}. See some more information at '''{{m|en|Roma}}'''.

The other major categories of words for the Roma are cognates of {{m|en|Gypsy}} (words related to [[Egypt]]) and cognates of {{m|en|tzigane}} (words derived from Greek); see those entries for more information.

Not related to {{m|en|Romanian}} or {{m|en|Roman}}.

